Terence Moore, known professionally as Terry Moore, is an English-born New Zealand musician and songwriter, best known as a former member of the Dunedin New Zealand band The Chills, for whom he played bass from 1981 to 1983, 1985–86 and again from 1991 to 1993.
He currently resides in Brooklyn, NY.
